org.middleheaven.util.collections
Class Range<T>

java.lang.Object
  org.middleheaven.util.collections.Interval<T>
      org.middleheaven.util.collections.Range<T>
Type Parameters:
T - the type of the value in the range.
All Implemented Interfaces:
Iterable<T>, Enumerable<T>, RandomEnumerable<T>, Walkable<T>
public class Range<T>
extends Interval<T>
implements Enumerable<T>, RandomEnumerable<T>

Provides range semantics and operations. A Range is like an Interval with iterator semantics over the interval values. An Incrementor is used to define how the iteration visits the values in the interval.

union

public Range<T> union(Interval<T> other)
The union of this range with an another. The result is a range from the lowest start to the greatest end Note that union is a commutative operation, meaning that R.union(S).equals(S.union(R)) == true , R and S being instances of Range.

Overrides:
union in class Interval<T>
Parameters:
other -
Returns:
a range from the lowest start to the greatest end. Example : [2,3] merged with [7,10] will return [2,10]
